args: I'll need this. Oh, and these, too.\nAnd thiiiis...? No, don't think I'll\nneed that.
Pietro? What are you up to?
Hey there, {player_name}.\nJust preparing to go to the frozen city.
I just finished assembling the gear I'll\nneed once I get there.
I have warm clothing, a tent, rations...\nOh, and THESE!
They're skis! A place called the frozen city\nwill definitely have some great powder,\nso I'm gonna need these puppies.
I was actually just about to take 'em for\na little trial run.
I'm not terribly familiar with skiing,\nbut don't you need snow in order to do it?\nWe're a long way from the mountains.
Don't you worry yourself about that.\nWhere there's a hill, there's a way!
I spotted some nice grassland nearby\nwhen I was wandering around earlier.
Well then, I suppose I'd better take\nadvantage of the chance while I have it.
Wooo! Oh yeah, that's the stuff.
Ha ha! Oh man, I'm gonna be golden once\nI reach the frozen city.
That woman is being attacked by a fiend!\nWe have to help her!
Pietro and his skis are on the case!
Brace yourself for this one, fiend! It's the\nPIETRO SUPERSONIC SKI ASSAULT!
Ha! How ya like them apples?!
Sure glad we made it in timeâ€”thanks to\nmy skis, of course.
Yeah, I suppose we would have been too\nlate without...
Hmm? What about it? ...OH, POOP!\nIt's broken clean in half!
Oh my goodness, I'm so sorry.\nThis is all my fault.
I understand that you're disappointed,\nPietro, but keep your head up.
Disappointed? Not in the slightest!\nOn the contrary, this a great experience.

If my skis got busted up in the middle of
an adventure, I'd be in a tough pickle.
But now I know exactly how much stress
they can take before snapping!
And THAT means I'll be able to avoid this\nlittle problem in the future, right?
I mean, sure, it's a LITTLE disappointing,\nbut that's what prep work is all about.
And it's all thanks to you, little lady!\nMuch appreciated.
Er, n-not at all. I'm grateful to you.
Heh. It seems optimism is really one of\nyour strengths, Pietro.
